WEBVTT

00:00.537 --> 00:01.936
<i>Previously on</i> Sanctuary...

00:02.246 --> 00:03.646
I've just shut down Wall Street

00:03.648 --> 00:04.848
for 12 minutes.

00:04.850 --> 00:05.749
I'm Caleb.

00:05.751 --> 00:06.818
As in Hollow Earth Caleb?

00:06.820 --> 00:07.787
The most wanted man,

00:07.789 --> 00:09.789
according to
human authorities.

00:09.791 --> 00:11.326
<i>Aiding and abetting</i>
<i>a known terrorist</i>

00:11.328 --> 00:12.561
<i>is tantamount to treason.</i>

00:12.563 --> 00:14.830
Caleb wants to end
this conflict,

00:14.832 --> 00:16.665
as do the other
Hollow Earth abnormals.

00:16.667 --> 00:18.368
We're making
a Homeland for them,

00:18.370 --> 00:19.804
starting immediately.

00:19.806 --> 00:21.505
You know I've always wanted
to be free.

00:21.507 --> 00:23.173
This is my chance.

00:23.175 --> 00:24.309
So you've made your decision.

00:24.311 --> 00:27.212
This is my home now.

00:27.214 --> 00:29.316
The Fifth Ward is becoming
ground zero in this war.

00:29.318 --> 00:31.184
Your boss just signed up
with the enemy.

00:31.186 --> 00:32.384
You're coming to work for me.

00:32.387 --> 00:34.221
This could actually
be useful,

00:34.223 --> 00:36.222
you working at SCIU,

00:36.224 --> 00:37.490
inside the belly of the beast,
so to speak.

00:37.492 --> 00:38.491
Your first assignment

00:38.493 --> 00:40.826
is to arrest
and detain Helen Magnus.

00:46.333 --> 00:47.532
Get out of the car!

00:47.534 --> 00:50.668
You really don't
want to do this, Will.

00:50.670 --> 00:51.736
You left me no choice.

00:53.538 --> 00:54.572
Magnus, don't do this.

00:54.574 --> 00:55.407
Sorry, Will.

01:01.281 --> 01:03.616
What the hell's
going on, Addison?

01:03.618 --> 01:04.818
Been in the planning
stages for a long time,

01:04.819 --> 01:06.421
just never seemed
logistically feasible.

01:06.423 --> 01:08.923
I mean, how do you coax
a large number of abnormals

01:08.925 --> 01:10.726
into one condensed area

01:10.728 --> 01:13.162
away from prying civilian eyes?

01:13.164 --> 01:14.664
Homeland...

01:14.666 --> 01:15.531
- <i>- We are live on the scene</i>

01:15.533 --> 01:16.766
<i>of what authorities are calling</i>

01:16.768 --> 01:18.200
<i>the largest</i>
<i>toxic industrial spill</i>

01:18.202 --> 01:19.668
<i>in recent history.</i>

01:19.670 --> 01:21.136
When did this
become a police state?

01:21.138 --> 01:22.471
It's always been
a police state, Will,

01:22.473 --> 01:23.939
you just never noticed.

01:23.941 --> 01:25.407
They just turned it
into a prison.

01:25.409 --> 01:27.475
Of course they have.

01:27.477 --> 01:28.843
Doc, where are you going?

01:28.845 --> 01:31.613
<i>This district</i>
<i>is full of strange beings</i>

01:31.615 --> 01:34.715
<i>who have lived among us</i>
<i>for hundreds of years.</i>

01:34.717 --> 01:36.517
What the hell is that
crazy broad doing now?

01:36.519 --> 01:37.618
<i>I call them abnormals.</i>

01:37.620 --> 01:38.620
Oh, Magnus...

01:38.622 --> 01:40.822
<i>You know them as monsters,</i>

01:40.824 --> 01:44.460
<i>and they very much exist.</i>

01:46.730 --> 01:48.632
I'm going to have to
call you back, General.

01:48.634 --> 01:50.234
Addison.

01:50.236 --> 01:52.770
Yes, Mr. President,
I'm sorry,

01:52.772 --> 01:54.004
I was just on with
the Joint Chiefs.

01:55.374 --> 01:56.608
I understand, sir.

01:56.610 --> 01:58.843
We're working up
scenarios right now.

02:00.346 --> 02:03.416
You will be my first call.

02:05.619 --> 02:07.621
I'm not even going
to bother asking

02:07.623 --> 02:08.955
if this was part of her plan.

02:08.957 --> 02:10.957
Oh, I had no idea
this was coming,

02:10.959 --> 02:13.594
but here's the deal,
neither did you.

02:13.596 --> 02:15.763
Trust me, it changes nothing.

02:15.765 --> 02:16.764
We'll bring the media in line.

02:16.766 --> 02:18.666
"Monsters exist"?

02:18.668 --> 02:19.634
Good luck with the spin.

02:19.636 --> 02:21.770
Are you still
not on board here?

02:21.772 --> 02:23.605
After the ass-kicking
she just gave you?

02:23.607 --> 02:25.607
Look...

02:25.609 --> 02:27.776
I'll take getting
beaten up by a girl

02:27.778 --> 02:31.247
over being the fall guy
to this mess any day.

02:34.018 --> 02:35.652
Addison.

02:36.887 --> 02:39.790
No, I assure you, Senator,

02:39.792 --> 02:41.791
we have the situation
well in hand.

02:47.665 --> 02:49.032
Hey.

02:49.034 --> 02:51.668
How's your head?

02:51.670 --> 02:53.002
<i>It'll heal.</i>

02:53.004 --> 02:55.037
My pride, however,
is another story.

02:55.039 --> 02:56.773
Ah, yes, well,
some things can't be helped.

02:56.775 --> 02:58.808
You know, I always said
you were crazy,

02:58.810 --> 03:00.543
but this?

03:00.545 --> 03:02.446
It was vital that Addison
and his agenda be derailed,

03:02.448 --> 03:04.448
at least momentarily.

03:04.450 --> 03:06.584
<i>Yeah, well,</i>
<i>that's happening.</i>

03:06.586 --> 03:08.486
Would you care
to explain why?

03:08.488 --> 03:10.688
Because creating a prison
isn't the final move here.

03:10.690 --> 03:12.524
<i>It will be</i>
<i>something far worse.</i>

03:12.526 --> 03:14.025
Come on,

03:14.027 --> 03:16.427
even Addison
wouldn't go that far.

03:16.429 --> 03:17.662
<i>Oh, the order</i>
<i>won't come from him.</i>

03:17.664 --> 03:18.930
<i>It'll come from</i>
<i>higher up.</i>

03:18.932 --> 03:22.901
Look, I realize this is
intolerable for you,

03:22.903 --> 03:24.469
but I need you to stay focused.

03:24.471 --> 03:26.705
You're in the right place
at the moment.

03:26.707 --> 03:28.307
To do what?

